"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from UK Public Health Register (HCP0007)              \n              \n              \n              \n              \nKey Issues&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nBackground&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nStatutory or voluntary regulation&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDevelopment of public health workforce&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nPublic safety&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n(a)\n&#xa0;&#xa0; \nWill HCPC expect these leaders in public health to fit in with HCPC’s existing approach to regulation which inevitably, given the large number of registrants, involves more of a “tick box” process?\n&#xa0;\n(b)\n&#xa0;&#xa0; \nHow will HCPC take account of the role of public health specialists, \ncarrying responsibility at a strategic level for protecting and enhancing the public's health, in differentiating an existing approach based largely on the regulation of practitioners who work individually with clients?\n&#xa0;\n(c) When will HCPC commence consultation with UKPHR in particular and the wider public health community as a whole to address the many complex issues that will arise on a change of regulator?\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDecember 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n Review of the Regulation of Public Health Professionals published in \nNovember 2010\n.\n Healthy Lives, Healthy People: A Public Health Workforce Strategy \nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/healthy-lives-healthy-people-a-public-workforce-strategy\n \n"